<br>
Say two guilds are planable, both have posting rights. Each has a turn that comes up once a month (just for arguments sake). That means that the members of each guild have only one chance per month of epic loot. BUT if the help each other, they can double their chances at that loot. Each one has one a month, so they are really going twice a month.<br>
<br>
By the rules of our system, if an alliance is formed between two guilds, their posting rights are changed to the alliance and not the individuals. So their raiding is done together.<br>
<br>
By making a “secret alliance” you would be giving your members extra chances. The Rathe is about giving equal chances to people, so the rule of 6 was created to maintain this.<br>
